<br>
Good: <br>
Hundreds of quests with some great rewards, making it a lot more dynamic, despite the fact the basic storyline is linear.<br>
Lots of nice equipment and weapons to choose from.<br>
Deeply immersive storyline.<br>
Random encounters only on the map,  and even those are in a separate &quot;zone&quot; where you get to pick your enemies (after a month of the constant &quot;whoosh.... dadadadadada dada dadadadadada dada&quot; of FF9, it makes a *very* welcome change)<br>
Very nice graphics... ooh those summons :)<br>
Nice simple spell system.  EXP = new spells.<br>
<br>
Bad:<br>
Poor camera angles.  It took me around 2-3 hours to learn my way around Lenele, which would have been a lot easier if the camera wasn't stuck on &quot;high&quot; and constantly rotating.<br>
Very little interaction between your own characters.  Some of the nice frienly chatter like in FF games would be nice. <br>
No rendered FMV of the characters, which I saw as a nice reward in FF7-9 when you progress through the story a bit.  But the painted cutscenes are still very good, and some of the boss battle intros look almost as good as a rendered FMV anyway.<br>
<br>
Overall - Highly recommended. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucloudanetrihart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cloudane Trihart</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=25869912&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/2/01 5:09:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1110.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks for the input</span><hr size=1> Oh yeah, if you want to try some of the Emulator stuff....<br>
